SIMPLE: indigestible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indigestible
<hw>In`di*gest"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indigestibilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indigestible</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Digest</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not digestible; not readily soluble in the digestive
juices; not easily convertible into products fitted for
absorption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not digestible in the mind; distressful;
intolerable; <as>as, an <ex>indigestible</ex> simile</as>.</def>
<rj><au>T. Warton.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In`di*gest"i*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In`di*gest"i*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>indigestibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
